description: Luke Humphries (born February 11, 1995 in Newbury) is a darts player from England who plays in the PDC tournaments. On October 8, 2023, he won his first main tournament with that association with the World Grand Prix. Later that year he also triumphed at the Grand Slam of Darts and Players Championship Finals. On January 3, 2024 he won the PDC World Darts Championship.

Michael van Gerwen (born 25 April 1989 in Boxtel) is a Dutch professional darts player. On January 1, 2014, he became the youngest player ever to win the PDC World Darts Championship, after reaching the final a year earlier. Winning this competition also ensured that he became number one in the world rankings for the first time. He is now a three-time world champion. Van Gerwen won his 71st PDC Pro Tour title on February 16, 2019, breaking the record of Phil Taylor, who won 70 Pro Tour titles in his career. In 2024, Van Gerwen is the only active PDC player who has won all current major tournaments one or more times.

Michael Smith (born 18 September 1990 in St. Helens), nicknamed 'Bully Boy', is an English darts player who plays for the Professional Darts Corporation (PDC). Smith won his first world title on January 3, 2023 during the 2023 PDC World Darts Championship, in which he won the final 7-4 in sets against Michael van Gerwen. In this final, Smith also threw a 9-darter and with this victory he took first place on the PDC Order of Merit. Smith previously reached the final of the PDC World Darts Championship twice, losing the finals to Michael van Gerwen (2019) and Peter Wright (2022) respectively. In 2022, Smith won his first major final after being runner-up eight times; he conquered the Grand Slam of Darts by beating fellow countryman Nathan Aspinall 16-5 in the final. Smith was the first darts player to win both the PDC World Youth Championship and the PDC World Darts Championship.

Nathan Aspinall (born 15 July 1991 in Stockport) is an English darts player. Aspinall joined the PDC in 2012 after retiring from football. He was a goalkeeper for Manchester United's youth team and then played as a semi-professional at Cheadle Town. The first PDC main draw he won was the UK Open in 2019. In 2018, Aspinall won the PDPA Players Championship Barnsley by beating Ryan Searle in the final. At the 2019 PDC World Darts Championship, Aspinall successively defeated Geert Nentjes, Gerwyn Price, Kyle Anderson, Devon Petersen and Brendan Dolan to reach the semi-finals. Here he lost 3-6 to Michael Smith. On March 3, 2019, Aspinall won the UK Open by beating Rob Cross 11-5 in legs in the final. This victory also meant that he ended up in the top 16 of the Order of Merit. At the 2020 World Cup, The Asp reached the semi-finals for the second year in a row.

Robert (Rob) Cross (born 21 September 1990 in Pembury) is an English professional darts player who plays for the PDC. He won the PDC World Darts Championship on January 1, 2018, after beating Phil Taylor 7-2 in sets in the final. On Sunday, July 28, 2019, Rob Cross won his second major at the PDC with the 2019 World Matchplay. In a final in which Cross led 9-0, Michael Smith was eventually defeated 18-13.

Gerwyn Price (born 7 March 1985 in Markham) is a darts player from Wales. He won the PDC World Darts Championship for the first time in his career on January 3, 2021, with Price also becoming number one in the world rankings for the first time in his career. As a result, Michael van Gerwen lost the leading position on the PDC Order of Merit after seven years. He won 7-3 in sets against former world champion Gary Anderson in the final.
David (Dave) Chisnall (born 12 September 1980 in St. Helens) is an English darts player in the tournaments of the Professional Darts Corporation. His nickname is Chizzy.

Peter Wright (born 10 March 1970 in Livingston) is a Scottish darts player. His nickname is Snakebite. Wright is best known for his colorful clothes, hairstyle and the snake head painted on his head by his own wife when he plays. On January 1, 2020, he became PDC world champion for the first time by winning the final 3–7 in sets against Michael van Gerwen. On January 3, 2022, Wright became PDC world champion for the second time by winning the final 5–7 in sets against Michael Smith. Wright became number one on the PDC Order of Merit for the first time on March 6, 2022.

Dimitri Van den Bergh (Antwerp, July 8, 1994), nicknamed The Dreammaker, is a Belgian darts player who plays in the Professional Darts Corporation competition (PDC). In 2017 and 2018 he became PDC youth world champion. With the World Matchplay in 2020 and the UK Open in 2024, Van den Bergh has two PDC major titles to his name.

Damon Heta (born August 10, 1987 in Perth) is an Australian darts player who plays for the PDC. He earned his 2020/2021 tour card by finishing fourth on the Q-School Order of Merit at the 2020 UK Q-School.
